PART A — AG31 / System/swarm_stochastic_corrector.py
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

VERDICT: Mechanism real, specific result (cooperator_ratio = 1.0000) is
         an artifact of a tautological fitness function. Salvageable
         with a one-line patch.

AG31's drop runs and reproduces 1.0000 exactly. But the load-bearing
line is

    fitness = A.astype(float) + 0.1

That is selection PROPORTIONAL TO COOPERATOR COUNT. It selects A
directly. With internal kinetics k_A=1.0 vs k_B=1.2, every cell is
pushed toward more B by intra-cellular replication; but as soon as
binomial fission noise hands a daughter B=0, the kinetic formula
p_a = k_A·A / (k_A·A + k_B·0) = 1 makes that cell pure-A forever
(absorbing state). Combined with selection-on-A, pure-A cells then
displace everyone else. The 1.0000 is a degenerate fixed point of
"fitness = A", not a stochastic balance.

I tested this by changing ONE LINE — replacing fitness=A+0.1 with
the actual Szathmáry-Demeter joint fitness fitness=min(A,B)+0.1 —
and re-running with identical seeds, kinetics, and capacity. Result:

    AG31 original (fitness = A):           A=2613, B=0,    ratio = 1.0000
    Joint   fitness (fitness = min(A,B)):  A=1065, B=1584, ratio = 0.4020
    Well-mixed soup (single big cell):     A=170,  B=3302, ratio = 0.0490

So the underlying compartmentalization mechanism IS real (8x rescue
under joint fitness) but AG31's 1.0000 is the wrong number for the
right mechanism. The drop is one line away from being publishable.
Other latent issues: pure-A is an absorbing state under the kinetics
(no mutation back), and the "well-mixed control" is a single cell
rather than 100 cells with mixed contents — apples to oranges.

